#. <section class="sutta" id="sn3.2"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn3.2:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.2:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. Shackles"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn3.2:0.3"
msgid "2. Purisasutta"
msgstr "2. A Man"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.162"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.2:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn3.2:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājā "
"pasenadi kosalo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then King Pasenadi of Kosala went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one "
"side, and said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn3.2:1.3"
msgid ""
"“kati nu kho, bhante, purisassa dhammā ajjhattaṃ uppajjamānā uppajjanti "
"ahitāya dukkhāya aphāsuvihārāyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, how many things arise inside a person for their harm, suffering, and "
"discomfort?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.2:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Tayo kho, mahārāja, purisassa dhammā ajjhattaṃ uppajjamānā uppajjanti "
"ahitāya dukkhāya aphāsuvihārāya."
msgstr ""
"“Great king, three things arise inside a person for their harm, suffering, "
"and discomfort."

msgctxt "sn3.2:2.2"
msgid "Katame tayo?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "sn3.2:2.3"
msgid ""
"Lobho kho, mahārāja, purisassa dhammo ajjhattaṃ uppajjamāno uppajjati "
"ahitāya dukkhāya aphāsuvihārāya."
msgstr "Greed,"

msgctxt "sn3.2:2.4"
msgid ""
"Doso kho, mahārāja, purisassa dhammo ajjhattaṃ uppajjamāno uppajjati ahitāya "
"dukkhāya aphāsuvihārāya."
msgstr "hate,"

msgctxt "sn3.2:2.5"
msgid ""
"Moho kho, mahārāja, purisassa dhammo ajjhattaṃ uppajjamāno uppajjati ahitāya "
"dukkhāya aphāsuvihārāya."
msgstr "and delusion."

msgctxt "sn3.2:2.6"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, mahārāja, tayo purisassa dhammā ajjhattaṃ uppajjamānā uppajjanti "
"ahitāya dukkhāya aphāsuvihārāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"These three things arise inside a person for their harm, suffering, and "
"discomfort.”"

msgctxt "sn3.2:2.7"
msgid "Idamavoca … pe …"
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. …"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.163"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.2:3.1"
msgid "“Lobho doso ca moho ca,"
msgstr "“When greed, hate, and delusion,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.2:3.2"
msgid "purisaṃ pāpacetasaṃ;"
msgstr "have arisen inside oneself,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.2:3.3"
msgid "Hiṃsanti attasambhūtā,"
msgstr "they harm a person of wicked heart,"

# See BB for readings.
#. <br>
#. VAR: samphalan”ti → sapphalanti (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn3.2:3.4"
msgid "tacasāraṃva samphalan”ti."
msgstr "as a reed is destroyed by its own fruit.”"
